Distribution. Known only from the type specimens collected near Merauke in West Papua (
Fig. 13
) where it is bycatch of an artisanal beach seine fishery for penaeid prawns. Found in very shallow water (< 1 m depth) close to the shoreline; offshore distribution unknown. Possibly more widely spread along the southern coasts of West Papua and probably also in Papua New Guinea . However, it was not collected from coastal northern Australia or deeper parts of the Arafura Sea, despite comprehensive surveys of the ichthyofauna in these areas being conducted.
